               <msContents class="#STM">
                  <summary><p>These two folios are a replica of the beginning of manuscript 1762 from the library of the <term xml:lang="sa">Mahārāja</term> of Bikaner. It was created by Palmyr Cordier, probably based on Sanscrit 1177, which contains a transcript of that manuscript as well as <ref target="https://gallica.bnf.fr/ark:/12148/btv1b100905830/f3">photographs</ref> of the beginning and the end. Although Cordier has closely copied the format of that manuscript, he has not created a perfect imitation — he has added punctuation, and he has written in his own hand, rather than trying to copy the hand of the original.</p>
<p>The <title xml:lang="sa">Gayadāsanidāna</title> forms part of the <title xml:lang="sa">Nyāyacandrikā</title>, a commentary by <persName xml:lang="sa">Gayadāsa</persName> on the <title xml:lang="sa">Suśrutasaṃhitā</title>, an ancient medical compendium. The Bikaner manuscript is the only known copy of the <title xml:lang="sa">Gayadāsanidāna</title>, the commentary on the <title xml:lang="sa">Nidānasthāna</title> chapter (Meulenbeld 1984, 28).</p></summary>
                  
